
test_version: User container to get binary versions of fboot, sboot and mw

Following commands are recognized:

  'f': Get fboot binary version
  's': Get sboot binary version
  'm': Get supervisor binary version

Load the container:

$ mwtest.py -c100 run test_version.img
Sending request to CMRT MW...
...MW status 0

Get fboot binary version:

$ cmtest data -f100 'f'
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 36 bytes OK
00000000: 32 30 32 33 2d 30 33 2d  31 33 2d 67 34 32 30 34  |2023-03-13-g4204|
00000010: 36 36 61 2d 73 79 73 74  65 73 74 2d 64 65 62 75  |66a-systest-debu|
00000020: 67 00 00 00                                       |g...|

Get sboot binary version:

$ cmtest data -f100 's'
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 36 bytes OK
00000000: 32 30 32 33 2d 30 33 2d  31 33 2d 67 34 32 30 34  |2023-03-13-g4204|
00000010: 36 36 61 2d 73 79 73 74  65 73 74 2d 64 65 62 75  |66a-systest-debu|
00000020: 67 00 00 00                                       |g...|

Get supervisor binary version:

$ cmtest data -f100 'm'
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 36 bytes OK
00000000: 32 30 32 33 2d 30 33 2d  31 33 2d 67 34 32 30 34  |2023-03-13-g4204|
00000010: 36 36 61 2d 73 79 73 74  65 73 74 2d 64 65 62 75  |66a-systest-debu|
00000020: 67 00 00 00                                       |g...|

To unload container:

$ mwtest.py -c100 unload
